shore skink
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a variable skink species which lives on the north-eastern coast of the North Island and nearby off shore islands; also sometimes the very similar, recently differentiated, tatahi skink.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Environment
Region:[none]
